      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The wind slabs of Friday represent the main danger. They can be released by a single winter sport participant in some cases. Mostly they are shallow, caution is to be exercised in particular adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls, and on steep slopes in particular above the tree line. <br/> On very steep shady slopes the avalanches can be triggered in deep layers of the snowpack. Slopes that have been little used this winter thus far are especially unfavourable. <br/> Maintaining distances between individuals and one-at-a-time descents are recommended. <br/> More natural avalanches are possible, even medium-sized ones.",
        "highlights": "The deep wind slabs of Friday remain in some cases prone to triggering."
