      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Friday: 10 to 30 cm of snow, and up to 40 cm in some localities, has fallen above approximately 1200 m. <br/> The fresh snow and especially the wind-blown snow drifts, both soft and hard, cover a thin layer of old snow and partly also surface hoar.  In some cases the wind slabs have bonded poorly with the old snowpack. <br/> Faceted weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on west, north and east facing slopes. <br/>"
      },
