        "comment": "The fresh and somewhat older wind slabs represent the main danger. <br/> Winter sport participants can release avalanches in some places. Mostly they are shallow. The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls and on steep, little used slopes. <br/> In some places avalanches can also be triggered in the old snowpack. These are medium-sized and can mostly only be released by large loads. <br/> Maintaining distances between individuals and one-at-a-time descents are recommended. <br/> Small to medium-sized dry snow slides and avalanches are possible.",
